    public interface ILayoutAlgorithm
    ILayoutAlgorithm describes the general interface for algorithms that perform a layout process on a LayoutGraph.

    The main method for invoking the layout calculation is applyLayout(LayoutGraph). Implementing classes will arrange the graph there.

    This class also provides keys to register IDataProviders with the graph that contain information about the nodes and edges in the graph. IDataProviders registered with LayoutKeys.NODE_ID_DPKEY and LayoutKeys.EDGE_ID_DPKEY contain unique identifiers for both nodes and edges. These identifiers allow for ensuring consistent results even if the order of nodes and edges was changed between two layout runs.
    The selection state of nodes and edges is stored in IDataProviders registered with the keys LayoutKeys.AFFECTED_NODES_DPKEY and LayoutKeys.AFFECTED_EDGES_DPKEY. Based on this information, the layout algorithm may reduce its calculations to the selected subset of nodes or edges.
